<title>
Precautions for CAN Communication System
</title>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
The length of a loose twist (1) in a twist pair wire harnesses of the CAN lines except around the connector (3) should be within 100 mm (3.9 in.). Refer to the circuit diagram to identify the CAN lines. Excessively loose lines are more susceptible to interference by electric noise.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I4JA01000002.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "42.932mm" ver = "01" gw = "196" gh = "105"/>
<callout>
<table frame = "all" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<tgroup cols = "2" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<colspec colnum = "1" colname = "1" colwidth = "0.315in"/>
<colspec colnum = "2" colname = "2" colwidth = "1.074in"/>
<tbody>
<row rowsep = "0">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
2.
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Control module
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</callout>
</figure>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Do not connect CAN line terminals using a bypass wire (1). Doing so makes the CAN line receive electric noise interference.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I4JA01000003.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "45.842mm" ver = "01" gw = "196" gh = "114"/>
</figure>
</item>
